She called him Magnus, right?
Yeah. Yes.

976
01:19:35.646 --> 01:19:39.867
Maybe I could go back to the house and put
the doll back while she's still at school.

977
01:19:40.067 --> 01:19:43.537
Tsk. No, I can't do that. Calm
down, Miss Honey. Really.

978
01:19:43.696 --> 01:19:45.619
It's gonna be okay, I promise.

979
01:19:45.948 --> 01:19:49.202
Sweetheart, you promised you wouldn't
go back in that house again.

980
01:19:49.368 --> 01:19:53.623
I didn't. I was on the garage
roof. I did it with my powers.

981
01:19:53.956 --> 01:19:56.505
Okay, on the garage
roof with your powers.

982
01:19:56.667 --> 01:20:00.046
All right, I need to think.
Let's see.

983
01:20:18.814 --> 01:20:20.908
Powers. Mm-hm.

984
01:20:27.114 --> 01:20:30.744
I think I've got them down.
Watch this.

985
01:20:49.094 --> 01:20:51.438
No more Miss Nice Girl.

986
01:20:53.599 --> 01:20:56.603
Get inside.
Inside! Quickly, run!

987
01:20:56.769 --> 01:20:59.773
Run! Get against the wall!
Against that wall. Quickly!

988
01:20:59.938 --> 01:21:01.736
Don't make me wait.

989
01:21:01.899 --> 01:21:03.993
Water!

990
01:21:04.943 --> 01:21:07.366
And hold the newt.

991
01:21:11.283 --> 01:21:13.786
Join the ranks. Move!

992
01:21:16.955 --> 01:21:21.131
I am here to teach
you all a lesson.

993
01:21:24.797 --> 01:21:30.224
Sometimes in life, horrible and
unexplainable things happen.

994
01:21:33.847 --> 01:21:38.193
These things are a
test of character.

995
01:21:42.481 --> 01:21:44.700
And I have character.

996
01:21:44.858 --> 01:21:49.409
Form a line across the room! Quickly!
Run, run, run! Don't keep me waiting.

997
01:21:49.822 --> 01:21:51.324
Fill this gap!

998
01:21:52.574 --> 01:21:57.000
I expect you're wondering
what I'm talking about. Hm?

999
01:21:57.496 --> 01:21:59.590
Yes.

1000
01:21:59.748 --> 01:22:03.093
A child came to my house.

1001
01:22:03.252 --> 01:22:07.007
I don't know how, I don't
know when, I don't know why.

1002
01:22:07.172 --> 01:22:09.846
Miss Trunchbull, may I...?
No, you may not.

1003
01:22:10.759 --> 01:22:13.979
But I know a child came.

1004
01:22:14.138 --> 01:22:17.859
So did you know it was illegal

1005
01:22:18.016 --> 01:22:21.691
to enter someone's home
without their permission?

1006
01:22:21.854 --> 01:22:25.700
Yes, Miss Trunchbull.
Sir.

1007
01:22:25.858 --> 01:22:28.077
Stand straight! Stomachs in!
Shoulders back!

1008
01:22:29.695 --> 01:22:32.198
Do any of you recognize...

1009
01:22:33.198 --> 01:22:34.871
this?

1010
01:22:36.785 --> 01:22:39.413
Let's play a game. Shall we?

1011
01:22:39.580 --> 01:22:45.053
Who was wearing a pretty
red hair ribbon yesterday

1012
01:22:45.210 --> 01:22:48.054
and isn't wearing one today?

1013
01:22:48.213 --> 01:22:51.308
Can you answer me that?

1014
01:22:51.467 --> 01:22:56.724
Who does this
disgusting ribbon belong to?

1015
01:22:58.015 --> 01:22:59.892
I shall personally see to it

1016
01:23:00.058 --> 01:23:03.562
that the demented, drooling,
slime-breathed little Lilliputian

1017
01:23:03.729 --> 01:23:06.403
who owns this disgusting ribbon

1018
01:23:06.565 --> 01:23:11.071
will never see the light
of day again. You.

1019
01:23:11.236 --> 01:23:14.786
Miss Trunchbull, I was the one who was
at your house last night. I know what...

1020
01:23:14.948 --> 01:23:18.748
I broke your arm once before,
I can do it again, Jenny.

1021
01:23:18.911 --> 01:23:21.460
I am not 7 years old
anymore, Aunt Trunchbull.

1022
01:23:24.249 --> 01:23:26.593
Shut your holes!

1023
01:23:26.752 --> 01:23:29.426
You will be put away in a place

1024
01:23:29.588 --> 01:23:34.344
where not even the crows can
land their droppings on you.

1025
01:23:34.593 --> 01:23:35.765
Look.

1026
01:23:36.929 --> 01:23:39.523
- The chalk.
- The chalk.

1027
01:23:39.681 --> 01:23:42.025
Chalk.
The blinds.

1028
01:23:46.605 --> 01:23:49.950
"A."
"Agatha...

1029
01:23:52.611 --> 01:23:55.160
this is Magnus.

1030
01:23:57.449 --> 01:23:59.497
Give my...

1031
01:23:59.660 --> 01:24:01.788
little Bumblebee...

1032
01:24:01.954 --> 01:24:05.003
her house...

1033
01:24:05.165 --> 01:24:06.963
"and her money."

1034
01:24:07.125 --> 01:24:10.470
Money?
"Then get out of town."

1035
01:24:10.629 --> 01:24:13.883
If you don't, I will get you.

1036
01:24:14.049 --> 01:24:18.099
I will get you like you got me.

1037
01:24:18.262 --> 01:24:20.356
"That is a promise."

1038
01:25:39.217 --> 01:25:41.970
No, no, Miss Trunchbull,
please don't throw him.

1039
01:25:52.022 --> 01:25:55.071
Woo-hoo-hoo! Woo-hoo!

1040
01:26:48.120 --> 01:26:50.464
- Lavender!
- Lavender!

1041
01:26:55.377 --> 01:26:58.221
Neat!
That's cool.

1042
01:27:07.931 --> 01:27:10.150
It's the Trunch.

1043
01:27:12.561 --> 01:27:15.781
Wow! Hey, you guys,
look at this.

1044
01:27:15.939 --> 01:27:17.566
Yes!

1045
01:27:20.527 --> 01:27:22.325
Let go.

1046
01:27:25.031 --> 01:27:29.787
Wow. Cool. I didn't
know I could do that.

1047
01:27:29.953 --> 01:27:32.001
Pretty good, huh?

1048
01:27:47.179 --> 01:27:49.352
Yeah!

1049
01:28:18.460 --> 01:28:23.216
And the Trunchbull was gone,
never to be seen or heard from,

1050
01:28:23.381 --> 01:28:26.180
never to darken a
doorway again.

1051
01:28:28.220 --> 01:28:30.894
Miss Honey moved back
into her father's house.

1052
01:28:31.056 --> 01:28:32.399
Teatime.

1053
01:28:32.557 --> 01:28:34.355
Of course, Matilda was
a frequent visitor.

1054
01:28:34.518 --> 01:28:38.944
Did you know that the heart of a mouse
beats at the rate of 650 times a minute?

1055
01:28:39.231 --> 01:28:42.280
My, where'd you learn that?
In a book.

1056
01:28:42.442 --> 01:28:44.234
It beats so fast, it
doesn't sound like

1057
01:28:44.258 --> 01:28:46.072
beating at all. It sounds
like it's humming.

1058
01:28:46.279 --> 01:28:49.408
A porcupine's heart beats
300 times a minute.

1059
01:28:49.991 --> 01:28:51.993
All right. Quick!

1060
01:28:52.494 --> 01:28:53.791
Hey, you.

1061
01:28:54.830 --> 01:28:57.834
Hey, we're leaving. Let's go.
Get in the car. Hurry up.

1062
01:28:58.291 --> 01:29:01.010
Let's wrap up these cookies.
Come on, we're leaving. Now.

1063
01:29:01.169 --> 01:29:02.842
I'd be happy to walk her home.

1064
01:29:03.171 --> 01:29:05.845
Well, nobody will be there.
We're moving to Guam.

1065
01:29:06.007 --> 01:29:07.509
Come on, let's go. Guam?

1066
01:29:07.676 --> 01:29:09.724
Daddy's not gonna be in the
auto business anymore.

1067
01:29:09.928 --> 01:29:12.181
I don't want to leave.

1068
01:29:12.347 --> 01:29:14.315
But we're going on a
permanent vacation.

1069
01:29:14.683 --> 01:29:17.277
Yeah, and we gotta beat the
speedboat salesmen to the airport.

1070
01:29:17.435 --> 01:29:21.030
I love it here. I love my
school. It isn't fair.

1071
01:29:21.189 --> 01:29:22.667
Miss Honey, please don't
let them take me.

1072
01:29:22.691 --> 01:29:24.113
Get in the car, Melinda.
Matilda.

1073
01:29:24.276 --> 01:29:26.404
Whatever. I want
to stay with Miss Honey.

1074
01:29:26.570 --> 01:29:28.368
Well, Miss Honey
doesn't want you.

1075
01:29:28.530 --> 01:29:30.624
Why would she want some
snotty, disobedient kid?

1076
01:29:30.782 --> 01:29:34.457
Because she's a spectacularly
wonderful child, and I love her.

1077
01:29:34.911 --> 01:29:38.336
Adopt me, Miss Honey.
You can adopt me.

1078
01:29:38.498 --> 01:29:40.626
Look, I don't have time
for all these legalities.

1079
01:29:40.792 --> 01:29:43.136
One second, Dad, I have
the adoption papers.

1080
01:29:43.295 --> 01:29:44.717
What?

1081
01:29:44.880 --> 01:29:47.258
Hey, where'd you get those?
From a book in the library.

1082
01:29:47.424 --> 01:29:49.722
I've had them since I was
big enough to Xerox.

1083
01:29:49.968 --> 01:29:52.096
Are you hearing this, Harry?

1084
01:29:53.555 --> 01:29:56.729
All you have to do is sign them.
I'll be an only child again.

1085
01:29:56.892 --> 01:30:00.863
Shut up! I can't think
with all these sirens.

1086
01:30:02.606 --> 01:30:04.825
What do you think, pumpkin?

1087
01:30:07.319 --> 01:30:10.323
You're the only daughter
I ever had, Matilda.

1088
01:30:10.488 --> 01:30:14.243
And I never understood
you, not one little bit.

1089
01:30:17.120 --> 01:30:19.339
Who's got a pen?

1090
01:30:20.999 --> 01:30:24.003
Here. Thanks.

1091
01:30:25.837 --> 01:30:27.754
And doing,
perhaps, the first decent

1092
01:30:27.778 --> 01:30:29.717
thing they ever did
for their daughter,

1093
01:30:29.883 --> 01:30:33.478
the Wormwoods signed
the adoption papers.

1094
01:30:33.845 --> 01:30:36.769
And here. Okay.

1095
01:30:39.559 --> 01:30:42.654
All right, come on. Here.
Turn around.

1096
01:30:45.507 --> 01:30:48.668
You're not gonna be calling us for support
payments or something like that, huh?

1097
01:30:48.693 --> 01:30:51.822
Oh, no, no. We'll have
everything we need. Don't worry.

1098
01:30:51.988 --> 01:30:54.036
All right, here. Let's roll.

1099
01:30:59.704 --> 01:31:00.751
Ciao.

1100
01:31:09.631 --> 01:31:12.009
So Harry
and Zinnia got away.

1101
01:31:12.175 --> 01:31:16.646
And as bad as things were before,
that's how good they became.

1102
01:31:19.891 --> 01:31:23.020
Miss Honey was made
principal of Crunchem Hall,

1103
01:31:23.186 --> 01:31:26.941
which had to add an upper school because
children never wanted to leave.

1104
01:31:27.107 --> 01:31:30.281
And Matilda found, to
her great surprise,

1105
01:31:30.443 --> 01:31:32.195
that life could be fun.

1106
01:31:32.362 --> 01:31:36.333
And she decided to have as
much of it as possible.

1107
01:31:36.491 --> 01:31:40.291
After all, she was
a very smart kid.

1108
01:31:54.759 --> 01:31:56.761
But the happiest
part of the story

1109
01:31:56.928 --> 01:31:59.147
is that Matilda and Miss Honey

1110
01:31:59.305 --> 01:32:02.149
each got what they
had always wanted.

1111
01:32:02.308 --> 01:32:04.982
A loving family.

1112
01:32:06.521 --> 01:32:10.492
And Matilda never had to
use her powers again.

1113
01:32:10.859 --> 01:32:13.783
Well, I mean, almost never.

1114
01:32:23.830 --> 01:32:26.458
Call me Ishmael.

1115
01:32:26.624 --> 01:32:29.628
Some years ago, never
mind how long precisely,

1116
01:32:29.794 --> 01:32:33.264
"having little or no money in my
purse and nothing particular to..."

